<TITLE> Ministers, war crimes agencies meet to set terms </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 28 (bdnews24.com)Ministers and members of the war crimes investigation and prosecution teams met on Sunday evening to work out the terms of reference for the investigation and trial procedures. The meeting, which began just before 7.30 pm, was taking place at the Indira Road residence of law minister Shafique Ahmed. Home minister Sahara Khatun, state minister for law Quamrul Islam, law and home secretaries, special investigators and prosecutors seen to arrive for the meeting. The government announced the long-awaited formation of the war crimes tribunal on Mar 25. The three-member tribunal, a seven-member investigating agency and 12-member panel of prosecutors are set to begin functioning formally from Monday. Tribunal chairman Justice Md Nizamul Huq, and members justice Fazle Kabir and justice AKM Zahir Ahmed took office Sunday; among the 12 prosecutors, Mosharraf Hossain Kajal and Sanjida Khanam also attended office. bdn
